>>0f399d18-6777-41a7-85cb-01696f51a8a5
Exploiting Spectre Over the Internet

Google has demonstrated exploiting the Spectre CPU attack remotely over the web:

    Today, we’re sharing proof-of-concept (PoC) code that confirms the practicality of Spectre exploits against JavaScript engines. We use Google Chrome to demonstrate our attack, but these issues are not specific to Chrome, and we expect that other modern browsers are similarly vulnerable to this exploitation vector. We have developed an interactive demonstration of the attack available at https://leaky.page/ ; the code and a more detailed writeup are published on Github here.

    The demonstration website can leak data at a speed of 1kB/s when running on Chrome 88 on an Intel Skylake CPU. Note that the code will likely require minor modifications to apply to other CPUs or browser versions; however, in our tests the attack was successful on several other processors, including the Apple M1 ARM CPU, without any major changes.

Tags: exploits, Google, vulnerabilities	

Posted on March 18, 2021 at 6:17 AM	• 19 Comments

posts.subject: Time for a divorce? Wishful thinking.
posts.body:

And any minecraft strategy which attacks the greater public will turn the public against you. Think about all those new laws on the books which allow motorists to drive over protesters when they attempt to manipulate. Why those many comments about substations and hillbillies are so cringe. There's no mood for it. Won't find any tolerance either.

Nope. The ONLY way is a difficult and deadly slugfest. Very personal...involving perps and families. Until they recognize they just can't win. Bit by bit tyrants and tyrant fomenters would be whittled down. An absolute reduction in their number - like clearing cancerous cells.

Needless to say, none of these McVeigh cancer cleaners would survive. And their families would need resolute protection from the tyrant's apparatus - forever.

This imperial government has festered because the public allowed it. There is no easy way out for correction, and tyrants ALWAYS hold the higher ground.

Try to imagine what this government of yours has done. Think they won't execute ALL their evils on you? Cleaning cancer is expensive. A price must be paid.

posts.subject: Corporations as citizens......
posts.body:
There is an argument floating around which suggests that the 1% bounced the hostility directed toward them...into all these recent racial jihads.

I find this argument persuasive. 

Ask yourself, would you get ANY help from Democrat or Republican while pushing through a competent law which absolutely stripped corporations of citizenship and proscribed a death penalty should they involve themselves in politics? You would certainly be on your own.

Which is why any proper cancer cleaning would involve the management and owners of corporations. Ignoring their attacks on the public just insures those attacks continue. 

They have no defense against a truly determined foe on a suicide mission. As their numbers dwindle, the public's authority grows.

posts.subject: Imagine being a little guy....
posts.body:
who just wished to send Kyle a few bux in his hour of need. Never thinking a news reporter will take that as a personal invitation to dox you.

Well Jason, turnaround is fair play. The attached list of addresses likely contains YOUR home. Enjoy!

Hint: I'd try West Jordan first.

And to station management: The stench of wokeness is strong in your company. May you find it as light a burden as others.

posts.subject: How many historical events root from hubris?
posts.body:
Worldwide, the harvest was down last year. Due to intense cold and never ceasing rain. With covid, without covid. Bad harvest was baked in.

And economic life was STILL under intense manipulation following the 2008 disaster. More than 10 years after events.....

Bad crops, productivity sinkholes, market manipulations, unbalanced budgets. No failures or punishments for perps. We saved them all for the public good.

Only one group was immune from the pain. And they pressed their advantage. Much of the nation's assets are now theirs.

When the Soviet Union dissolved, little people were given shares in publicly owned enterprises. Took only a decade for them to lose those shares to oligarchs.

You are a serf. They won. Think of that the next time your betters instruct you. The instructions of late have been endless. Punishments too. Then again, which is worse? The voracious appetite of the oligarchs? Or their paid servants in Congress? Could any of this have happened without them?
